title: Power Outages Data Analysis
description: Analyzed a Purdue LASCI dataset on U.S. power outages (2000-2016). Cleaned data and performed univariate, bivariate, and NMAR analysis. Conducted permutation tests to analyze missingness dependency. Ran a hypothesis test to examine climate region distribution across cause categories. Built and evaluated a Random Forest Classifier to predict outage causes, using F1-score and accuracy for performance and GridSearchCV for hyperparameter tuning. Conducted a fairness analysis via permutation test to check for bias toward states of varying populations.

title: Meteorite Landings Analysis
description: Analyzed meteorite landing locations using hypothesis testing, random sampling, TVD, and confidence intervals using bootstrapping and CLT.

title: Taylor Swift Song Analysis
description: Analyzed Taylor Swift's songs using lyrics and audio features. Created data visualizations with Matplotlib to explore audio trends and built a song recommender, lyric searcher, and keyword identifier to find similar songs, search lyrics, and summarize key themes.
